            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains photostats of letters from Peter Lavis of Milwaukee, Wisc., to his wife and family. The letters, written in German, discuss the Know-Nothing movement and Lavis&#039;s service in the Wisconsin legislature, 1854-56.</p>
                                 <p>The Wisconsin Historical Society holds a duplicate set of these letters For the context of this correspondence, see Joseph Schafer, &quot;Know-Nothingism in Wisconsin,&quot; <emph render="italic">Wisconsin Magazine of History, </emph>8:1 (Sept. 1924), 3-21.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


